tables are organized in schemas
Display a string "SQL" select "hello": select 'hello'
Display three numbers {5,10,15} in three columns: select 5,10,15
Display sum of two numbers 10 and 15: select 10+15
Default order: ascending
order by can only be used in outer query
between 1980 and 1989 includes both years
if query has 'having' statement, it should ALWAYS be preceded by group by
you dont need group by in this statement: select count(name), count(mobile) from teacher

case when can be used in order by statement: ORDER BY CASE WHEN subject IN ('Chemistry','Physics') THEN 1 ELSE 0 END, subject, winner
